D(P_{1},P_{2}) = \frac{1}{2} \sum_{r}^{D} |Pr(r|1) - Pr(r|2) |
\sum_{r} P(r|1) = 1
\sum_{r} P(r|2) = 1
P(r|1) = \left\{ P(1|1),P(2|1),P(3|1),P(4|1)\right\}
P(r|2) = \left\{ P(1|2),P(2|2),P(3|2),P(4|2)\right\}
D(P_{1},P_{2}) = |Pr(1|1) - Pr(1|2)|+|Pr(2|1) - Pr(2|2)|+|Pr(3|1) - Pr(3|2)|+|Pr(4|1) - Pr(4|2)|
D(P_{1},P_{2}) = |[Pr(1|1)+Pr(2|1)]-[Pr(1|2)+Pr(2|2)]|+\\ |[Pr(3|1)+Pr(4|1)]-[Pr(3|2)+Pr(4|2)]|
D(P_{1},P_{2})=0
